verbose_text: Before 2008-2009 seasonal flu vaccination, sera from all 12 donors exhibited no detectable levels of neutralization titers against all three strains; while after 2008-2009 seasonal flu vaccination, sera from 8 of 12 donors exhibited neutralization activity at the serum dilution from 1:10 to 1:160 against H1N1 strain; but still none of them have measurable neutralization activity against 2 H5N1 strains (XREF_TABLE), even though neutralization activity against H5N1 pseudotypes expressing H5HA isolated from the same two H5N1 strains was detected by PN entry assay (XREF_TABLE).
